18 (b) A person may not engage in:
19 (1) sexual contact with another without the consent of the other;
20 (2) except as provided in § 3–307(a)(4) of this subtitle, a sexual act with
21 another if the victim is 14 or 15 years old, and the person performing the sexual act is at
22 least 4 years older than the victim; or
23 (3) except as provided in § 3–307(a)(5) of this subtitle, vaginal intercourse
24 with another if the victim is 14 or 15 years old, and the person performing the act is at least
25 4 years older than the victim.
